<db:para>The QML runtime automatically loads a translation from the i18n subdirectory of the root QML file, based on the system language.</db:para>
<db:para>The files are created or updated by running:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">lupdate qml-i18n.qml -ts i18n/base.ts
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>Translations for new languages are created by copying <db:emphasis>i18n/base.ts</db:emphasis> to <db:emphasis>i18n/qml_&lt;lang&gt;.ts</db:emphasis> The .ts files can then be edited with <db:link xlink:href="qtlinguist-index.xml">Qt Linguist</db:link>:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">linguist i18n/qml_fr.ts
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>The run-time translation files are then generated by running:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">lrelease i18n/*.ts
</db:programlisting>
<db:note>
<db:para>On Android, please make sure to include the generated *.qm files as resources.</db:para>
</db:note>
